Table S15. Comparison of calculated RMSD from experimental measurements for 30-µs simulations of Ash1. Rg penalties were computed using an experimental value of 28.5 ± 3.4.51 Chemical shifts (CS) are reported in ppm, Rg is in Å, and the scores are unitless. We note that in the case of the negatively charged protein Ash1 (net charge of −15 at pH 7), the Rg of the simulated ensembles obtained with C22* and C36m were substantially more expanded than the ensemble obtained with a99SB*-ILDN in TIP3P, and were in much better agreement with experiment. This suggests that charge-driven chain expansion is better captured by these CHARMM force fields.

