Figure S2. Comparison of helical propensities in a99SB*-ILDN/TIP3P simulations of NTAIL and the NTAIL MoRE. The helical propensity for the full NTAIL domain is shown in magenta, and the propensity for the residually helical molecular recognition element (NTAIL MoRE, residues 87– 117) is shown in blue. The experimental estimate from a restrained ensemble model73 calculated from NMR data is shown in black. The 30-residue NTAIL MoRE construct is too small to experience a restrictive hydrophobic collapse, resulting in helical propensities in much closer agreement with experiment.
