Figure S4. Performance of a99SB-ILDN-Q force field with torsions optimized targeting (AAQAA)3 fraction helicity and Ala5 scalar couplings as described previously.63 (A) Temperature-dependent helix fraction of (AAQAA)3. Helical propensities observed in simulations (red lines) of the disordered proteins (B) NTAIL MoRE, (C) drkN SH3, (D) ACTR, (E) NTAIL, (F) α-synuclein. Black lines are experimental estimates calculated from restrained ensemble models calculated from NMR data (NTAIL MoRE, NTail73 drkN SH329) or predicted from experimental NMR chemical shifts using the program δ2d74 (ACTR, α-synuclein). Through several attempts, we found that matching helicity of (AAQAA)3 resulted in too much helicity in disordered proteins, and ultimately accepted a model that does not closely reproduce the helicity of (AAQAA)3.
